  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health and WASH assistance to vulnerable communities affected by flooding. This UNICEF project provides access to fresh water to flood-affected households, distributes WASH kits, and constructs emergency showers and latrines. The project provides life-saving assistance to 18,500 people, including 4,340 women, 4,1700 men, 9,990 children, and 2,774 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
